'''-onomy''' is an [[English language|English]] [[suffix]] most commonly denoting an area of knowledge that studies laws of nature or physics.
It comes from [[Greek language|Greek]], and means "management" or "measurement". 

==List==

* [[agronomy]] (agriculture)
* [[astronomy]] (stars)
* [[autonomy]] (political)
* [[deuteronomy]] (biblical)
* [[Economics|economy]] (finance)
* [[gastronomy]] (food)
* [[isonomy]] (law)
* [[taxonomy]] (classification)

